# Never Strip the Site When Fixing

- **Never** remove or replace the full layout, nav, Footer, or homepage to "fix" a bug or blank page.
- **Never** serve static HTML from middleware instead of the real Next.js app to "fix" rendering.
- **Never** reduce the app to a minimal shell (bare html/body, no nav, no globals.css) to debug.
- **Fix only the broken part:** one route, one API, one component. Leave the rest of the site intact.
- If the cause is unclear, add logging, check Vercel logs, or add a small diagnostic—do not strip the live site.
